---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const title = 'Terms of Service'
const description =
  'The terms that govern your use of ghspictograms.com, including editorial-reference scope, affiliate relationships, warranty, and liability.'
const canonical = 'https://ghspictograms.com/terms/'

export const prerender = true
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="text-[#062A78] hover:underline">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">→</span>
      <span class="text-gray-700">Terms of Service</span>
    </nav>

    <h1
      class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight"
      style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif"
    >
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
      The terms below govern your use of ghspictograms.com. By using this site, you agree to these terms.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: 13 June 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">1. About these terms</h2>
        <p>
          These terms govern use of the website ghspictograms.com (the "site"), operated by GHS
          Pictograms from Riga, Latvia. By accessing or using the site, you agree to be bound by
          these terms. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">2. Purpose of the site</h2>
        <p>
          GHS Pictograms publishes an independent reference for GHS hazard classification and
          chemical safety compliance — including the Compliance Hub (UN GHS, OSHA HCS, CLP, SDS,
          REACH, and SVHC), a substance database, label and inspection tools, and explanatory
          content. The site is intended for EHS (environmental, health, and safety) professionals,
          compliance and procurement teams, and others responsible for chemical hazard
          communication in a business context.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may earn affiliate commissions when readers purchase or subscribe to tools and
          services we link to, at no additional cost to the reader. We do not author, sell, or
          fulfil safety data sheets or labels on a reader's behalf. See our
          <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="text-[#062A78] font-semibold hover:underline">Affiliate disclosure</a> for details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">3. Editorial content is reference, not professional advice</h2>
        <p>
          Content on this site — including the Compliance Hub articles, substance data, tools, and
          explanatory material — is published for general reference. It is not legal advice,
          regulatory advice, engineering advice, or a substitute for professional consultation
          specific to your jurisdiction and use case.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Chemical hazard communication is regulated under multiple frameworks (UN GHS; OSHA HCS in
          the US; CLP and REACH in the EU; and transport rules such as ADR, IMDG, and IATA).
          Regulations change over time. Before making a classification, labelling, or compliance
          decision, consult the original regulation text and, where appropriate, a qualified
          compliance professional.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">4. Affiliate relationships</h2>
        <p>
          The site contains links to third-party tools and service providers, including affiliate
          links. When a reader makes a purchase or subscribes through an affiliate link, GHS
          Pictograms may earn a commission at no additional cost to the reader.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Affiliate links are marked with a dagger symbol (&dagger;) and pages containing them
          display an affiliate disclosure. Editorial content is not determined by commission rates —
          see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="text-[#062A78] font-semibold hover:underline">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for the full policy.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We are not the seller of any product or service reached via an affiliate link. The terms
          of sale, subscription, warranty, and support are governed by the relevant provider.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">5. User submissions</h2>
        <p>
          When you submit an email enquiry or subscription, you confirm that the information
          provided is accurate and that you have the authority to provide it. Submissions are
          processed in accordance with our
          <a href="/privacy/" class="text-[#062A78] font-semibold hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We reserve the right to decline to respond to any submission, including those that appear
          to be automated, abusive, or not made in good faith.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">6. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All editorial content on the site — including articles, the substance database
          presentation, original graphics, and the GHS Pictograms name and logo — is the
          intellectual property of GHS Pictograms unless otherwise attributed. You may quote short
          extracts for non-commercial purposes with attribution and a link to the source page.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The GHS pictograms themselves are published by the United Nations as part of the GHS and
          are not proprietary to us. Third-party logos, product images, and trademarks shown on the
          site are the property of their respective owners and are used for identification and
          editorial commentary purposes. Use of such marks does not imply endorsement by the
          trademark owner.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">7. No warranty</h2>
        <p>
          The site is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We take reasonable care to
          ensure information is accurate at the time of publication, but we do not warrant that the
          site or its content is error-free, complete, current, or fit for any particular purpose.
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, we disclaim all implied warranties of
          merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">8. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, GHS Pictograms and its operators will
          not be liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising out
          of or in connection with use of the site, including loss of profits, business
          interruption, or loss of data, even if advised of the possibility of such damages. In all
          cases our aggregate liability is limited to one hundred euros (EUR 100) or the total fees
          you have paid us in the preceding twelve months, whichever is higher.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">9. Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          The site links to third-party websites operated by tool providers, regulators, and other
          parties. We do not control those sites and are not responsible for their content,
          accuracy, or practices. A link does not constitute endorsement of the linked site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">10. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms when our services or applicable laws change. The "Last updated"
          date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Material changes will be
          highlighted via a notice on the site. Continued use of the site after a revision
          constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">11. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of Latvia. Any dispute arising out of
          or in connection with these terms or use of the site will be subject to the exclusive
          jurisdiction of the courts of Latvia, without prejudice to consumer rights you may have
          under the law of your habitual residence within the European Union.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">12. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:sergejssevcenko@ghslabels.com" class="text-[#062A78] font-semibold hover:underline">sergejssevcenko@ghslabels.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">These terms of service were last updated on 13 June 2026.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
